Planning and Execution

Set up channels for collecting customer feedback, such as surveys, user interviews, or feedback forms on your website. Analyze this feedback to gain insights into what customers like and dislike about your product.
Advice: Use the feedback to inform future planning and execution. Incorporate customer insights into the development process.
Establish a system for collecting and analyzing feedback
This could involve setting up quality assurance processes, such as regular code reviews, automated testing, and performance monitoring.
Advice: Use the control measures to maintain product quality. Regularly review and update these measures based on changes in customer requirements or project goals.
Implement control measures to ensure product meets customer requirements

After testing your product, gather and analyze the results to identify areas for improvement. This could involve looking at which features are not working as expected, or where users are experiencing difficulties.
Advice: Use the analysis to inform future development. Incorporate the identified improvements into the next development cycle.
Analyze test results and make improvements

Use techniques such as the 5 Whys or Fishbone Diagram to identify the root causes of any issues in your current process. This involves asking why a problem occurred, and then continuing to ask why that happened, until you reach the root cause.
Advice: Use the root cause analysis to make improvements to the process. Incorporate these improvements into the next development cycle.
Analyze the process to identify root causes of issues

Start by identifying the needs and expectations of your customers. This can be done through customer interviews, surveys, or market research. Once you have a clear understanding of what your customers want, you can set project goals that align with these needs.
Advice: Use the defined project goals and customer requirements to guide the development process. Regularly review and update these based on changes in customer needs or market trends.
Define project goals and customer requirements
